OL,3,CMajority of UK rivers in poor
OL,4,Cecological health, citizen scientists
OL,5,Cfind
OL,7,FEarthwatch said 75% of tests showed
OL,8,Fthe rivers tested across the UK were
OL,9,Fin poor ecological health, rising to
OL,10,F89% in the Thames and Anglia regions.
OL,12,FHertfordshire and Cambridgeshire had
OL,13,Fthe worst water quality, with 91% and
OL,14,F89% of unacceptable levels of nutrient
OL,15,Fpollution, according to the findings.
OL,17,FBut Derbyshire and Northumberland had
OL,18,Fthe least nutrient pollution, with
OL,19,Fboth counties having 0% unacceptable
OL,20,Fdata sets.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
